/li>\n  <li>shares</li>\n  <li>intellectual property, eg trademarks, registered designs and patents</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>If you were a director or shareholder of a dissolved company, you may be able to <a href=\"/restore-dissolved-company\" title=\"Restore your dissolved company\">restore the company</a> without a court order.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Claiming or buying assets</h2>\n\n<p>You may be able to claim or buy assets from the dissolved company if:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>they owe you money - by getting a <a href=\"/claiming-money-or-property-from-dissolved-company/claiming-money-youre-owed\" title=\"court order to restore the company\">court order to restore the company</a></li>\n  <li>you&rsquo;re someone affected by the company closing - by <a href=\"/claiming-money-or-property-from-dissolved-company/buying-a-dissolved-companys-assets\" title=\"referring their assets\">&lsquo;referring&rsquo; their assets</a></li>\n  <li>you were a shareholder - by applying for a <a href=\"/claiming-money-or-property-from-dissolved-company/discretionary-grants-for-shareholders\" title=\"Discretionary grants\">discretionary grant</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/claiming-money-or-property-from-dissolved-company/claiming-money-youre-owed","slug":"claiming-money-youre-owed","order":2,"title":"Claiming money you're owed","body":"<p>If you&rsquo;re owed money by a dissolved company, you can apply for a court order to have the company restored. This is the first step in trying to get your money back.</p>\n\n<h2>Court order restoration</h2>\n\n<p>You may be able to apply for a court order to restore a company if:  </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you did business with them </li>\n  <li>you worked for them</li>\n  <li>they owed you money when they were dissolved</li>\n  <li>you&rsquo;re responsible for their employee pension fund</li>\n  <li>you have a shared or competing interest in land</li>\n  <li>you were a shareholder or director when it was dissolved</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Except in cases of personal injury, you need to apply within 6 years of the company being dissolved.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You can get <a href=\"/get-information-about-a-company\" title=\"Get information about a dissolved company\">information about a dissolved company</a> from Companies House.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>How to apply</h2>\n\n<p>Use form N208 to apply for court order restoration in England and Wales.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://hmctsformfinder.bl.justice.gov.uk/courtfinder/forms/n208-eng.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Form 208, claim to restore by court order'\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Form 208, claim to restore by court order’ (PDF, 117KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://hmctscourtfinder.justice.gov.uk/courtfinder/forms/n208a-eng.pdf\" title=\"How to complete the form to have a company restored\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Form 208a, guidance notes’ (PDF, 437KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Send your completed form to the nearest county court to the company&rsquo;s registered office that deals with bankruptcy (select &lsquo;County Court&rsquo; under &lsquo;Search by court type&rsquo; in the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://hmctscourtfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/\" title=\"Her Majesty’s Courts &amp; Tribunal Service\">court finder</a>), or the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://hmctscourtfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/Search.do?court_id=716\" title=\"Royal Courts of Justice\">Royal Courts of Justice.</a></p>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll also need to include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the court fee (cash, postal order or cheque made payable to Her Majesty’s Courts &amp; Tribunal Service)</li>\n  <li>a witness statement, containing the supporting information outlined in section 4 of the Treasury Solicitor&rsquo;s guide to company restoration</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>See the &lsquo;guide to company restoration&rsquo; for information about restoring a company.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.tsol.gov.uk/Publications/Scheme_Publications/company_restoration_Oct_2011.pdf\" title=\"How to apply to have a company restored\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Guide to company restoration’ (PDF, 624KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>In Scotland</h3>\n\n<p>Apply to the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.scotcourts.gov.uk/locations/index.asp?crt=sup_cos&amp;val=contact\" title=\"Contact details for Scottish Court of Session\">Court of Session</a> if initial value of the company&rsquo;s shares that have been paid for (&lsquo;paid-up capital&rsquo;) is more than £120,000.</p>\n\n<p>For other companies, apply to the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.scotcourts.gov.uk/locations/index.asp\" title=\"Scottish court locations\">local sheriff court.</a></p>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll then have to serve a &lsquo;petition to restore&rsquo; on the Registrar of Companies in Scotland, and any other bodies the court asks you to.</p>\n\n<h3>In Northern Ireland</h3>\n\n<p>Apply by serving an &lsquo;originating summons&rsquo; on the Royal Courts of Justice:</p>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\nRoyal Courts of Justice\n<br />Chichester Street\n<br />Belfast \n<br />BT1 3JY\n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n\n<p>You also need to send this to the Registrar of Companies in Northern Ireland, along with a witness statement in support of the application.</p>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\nThe Registrar of Companies\n<br />Companies House\n<br />Second Floor\n<br />The Linenhall\n<br />32-38 Linenhall Street\n<br />Belfast \n<br />BT2 8BG\n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Applying for court order restoration is complicated. You should <a href=\"http://www.lawsociety.org.uk/choosingandusing/findasolicitor.law\" title=\"find a solicitor on the Law Society website\" rel=\"external\">get legal advice</a> before applying.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>What happens next</h2>\n\n<p>If your claim is accepted, the court will issue an Order to restore the company - you&rsquo;ll be sent this, and you must send it on to the Registrar of Companies. Once they have it they will restore the company.</p>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll then need to take further action to try and get your money:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>get a &lsquo;judgment&rsquo; from court for the amount of the money you&rsquo;re owed together with interest and costs</li>\n  <li><a href=\"/statutory-demands\" title=\"Issue a statutory demand\">issue a statutory demand</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/wind-up-a-company-that-owes-you-money\" title=\"take out a winding up petition\">take out a winding up petition</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/claiming-money-or-property-from-dissolved-company/buying-a-dissolved-companys-assets","slug":"buying-a-dissolved-companys-assets","order":3,"title":"Buying a dissolved company's assets","body":"<p>If you want to claim or buy an asset belonging to a dissolved company, you may be able to do this by &lsquo;referring&rsquo; the asset to the body representing the Crown. This depends on where the company was registered.</p>\n\n<p>Anybody can refer an asset, including if:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you&rsquo;re the leaseholder of a property where the freehold was owned by the company</li>\n  <li>you want to buy or are affected by land owned by the company</li>\n  <li>you want to buy other assets held by the company like shares, trade marks or copyrights</li>\n  <li>you&rsquo;re a shareholder trying to get cash held by the company</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>How to refer an asset</h2>\n\n<p>In England and Wales (but not Cornwall or Lancashire), the Treasury Solicitor looks after dissolved company assets. Use the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.bonavacantia.gov.uk/output/dissolved-company-notification-form.aspx\" title=\"dissolved company notification form\">dissolved company notification form</a> to refer an asset to the Treasury Solicitor.</p>\n\n<p>You can also write to:</p>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\nTreasury Solicitor's Office (BV)\n<br />1 Kemble Street\n<br />London \n<br />WC2B 4TS\n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n\n<h2>Other bodies that represent the Crown</h2>\n\n<p>Elsewhere, dissolved companies&rsquo; assets are dealt with by:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>in Cornwall and Lancashire - <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.farrer.co.uk/\" title=\"Farrer and Co\">Farrer and Co</a></li>\n  <li>in Scotland - <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://qltr.gov.uk/content/bona-vacantia\" title=\"The Queen's and Lord Treasurer's Remembrancer\">The Queen&rsquo;s and Lord Treasurer&rsquo;s Remembrancer</a></li>\n  <li>in Northern Ireland - phone or write to the Crown Solicitor&rsquo;s Office for Northern Ireland</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Crown Solicitor’s Office for Northern Ireland</strong>  </p>\n\n<p><strong>Phone:</strong> 028 9054 6037</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\nCrown Solicitor\n<br />Royal Courts of Justice\n<br />Chichester Street\n<br />Belfast \n<br />BT1 3JY\n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/claiming-money-or-property-from-dissolved-company/discretionary-grants-for-shareholders","slug":"discretionary-grants-for-shareholders","order":4,"title":"Discretionary grants for shareholders","body":"<p>You may be able to get back a dissolved company&rsquo;s assets if you were one of its shareholders - apply for a discretionary grant.</p>\n\n<h2>How to apply</h2>\n\n<p>In England and Wales (but not Cornwall or Lancashire) you must apply to the Treasury Solicitor.</p>\n\n<p>Send an application form and a statutory declaration to the Treasury Solicitor&rsquo;s Office.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><strong>If the company can be restored</strong>  </p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://www.bonavacantia.gov.uk/upload/DG2.doc\" title=\"Download 'Form DG2 - Application for a discretionary grant if the company can be restored' (D