a holding deposit (money you pay to ‘hold’ a property before an agreement is signed). However, once you become a tenant, the holding deposit becomes a deposit, which they must protect.</p>\n\n<h2>Deposits made by a third party</h2>\n<p>Your landlord must use a <abbr title=\"Tenancy deposit protection\">TDP</abbr> scheme even if your deposit is paid by someone else, like a rent deposit scheme or your parents.</p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/tenancy-deposit-protection/information-landlords-must-give-tenants","slug":"information-landlords-must-give-tenants","order":2,"title":"Information landlords must give tenants","body":"<p>Within 30 days of getting your deposit, your landlord must tell you:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the address of the rented property </li>\n  <li>how much deposit you&rsquo;ve paid</li>\n  <li>how the deposit is protected</li>\n  <li>the name and contact details of the <abbr title=\"Tenancy deposit protection\">TDP</abbr> scheme and its dispute resolution service</li>\n  <li>their (or the letting agency&rsquo;s) name and contact details</li>\n  <li>the name and contact details of any third party that&rsquo;s paid the deposit</li>\n  <li>why they would keep some or all of the deposit</li>\n  <li>how to apply to get the deposit back</li>\n  <li>what to do if you can&rsquo;t get hold of the landlord at the end of the tenancy</li>\n  <li>what to do if there&rsquo;s a dispute over the deposit</li>\n</ul>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/tenancy-deposit-protection/if-your-landlord-doesnt-protect-your-deposit","slug":"if-your-landlord-doesnt-protect-your-deposit","order":3,"title":"If your landlord doesn't protect your deposit","body":"<p>If you&rsquo;re not sure whether your deposit has been protected, ask your landlord or contact the approved schemes:</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Deposit Protection Service</strong><br />\n0844 4727 000</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>MyDeposits</strong><br />\n0844 980 0290</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Tenancy Deposit Scheme</strong><br />\n0845 226 7837<br />\n<a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#100;&#101;&#112;&#111;&#115;&#105;&#116;&#115;&#064;&#116;&#100;&#115;&#046;&#103;&#098;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#109;\">&#100;&#101;&#112;&#111;&#115;&#105;&#116;&#115;&#064;&#116;&#100;&#115;&#046;&#103;&#098;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#109;</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Getting your deposit back</h2>\n<p>If you think your landlord hasn&rsquo;t used a <abbr title=\"Tenancy deposit protection\">TDP</abbr> scheme when they should have, you can apply to a county court. </p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p><a href=\"http://legaladviserfinder.justice.gov.uk/AdviserSearch.do\" title=\"Find a legal adviser\" rel=\"external\">Get legal advice</a> before applying to court.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>If the court finds your landlord hasn’t protected your deposit, it can order the person holding the deposit to either:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>repay it to you</li>\n  <li>pay it into a custodial <abbr title=\"Tenancy deposit protection\">TDP</abbr> scheme’s bank account within 14 days</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The court may also order the landlord to pay you up to 3 times the deposit within 14 days of making the order. </p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p><a href=\"http://hmctscourtfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS\" title=\"Find a court\" rel=\"external\">Search for a county court.</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>At the end of the tenancy</h2>\n<p>If your landlord doesn&rsquo;t use a <abbr title=\"Tenancy deposit protection\">TDP</abbr> scheme when they have to, the court may also decide that you won&rsquo;t have to leave the property when the tenancy ends.</p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/tenancy-deposit-protection/disputes-and-problems","slug":"disputes-and-problems","order":4,"title":"Disputes and problems","body":"<h2>If there’s a dispute over a deposit</h2>\n<p>If you disagree with your landlord about how much deposit should be returned, then your <abbr title=\"Tenancy deposit protection\">TDP</abbr> scheme offers a free dispute resolution service.</p>\n\n<h2>If you can&rsquo;t contact the landlord</h2>\n<p>If your landlord is registered with the Deposit Protection Service (DPS) you can <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.depositprotection.com/\" title=\"Deposit Protection Service\">make a single claim</a> to recover the deposit.</p>\n\n<p>If the scheme can&rsquo;t get in contact with the landlord, you get your deposit back.</p>\n\n<p>If your landlord is registered with <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.mydeposits.co.uk/tenants/get-started/register-a-dispute/\" title=\"Raise a dispute with MyDeposits\">MyDeposits</a> or the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.thedisputeservice.co.uk/raise-a-dispute.html\" title=\"Raise a dispute with TDS\">Tenancy Deposit Scheme (TDS)</a> you can ‘raise a dispute&rsquo; to recover the deposit.</p>\n\n<p>The scheme&rsquo;s insurer will refund your deposit if the dispute resolution service agrees this is fair.</p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/tenancy-deposit-protection/get-help-and-advice","slug":"get-help-and-advice","order":5,"title":"Get help and advice","body":"<p>You can get more help and advice from the following organisations.</p>\n\n<p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.citizensadvice.org.uk/index/getadvice.htm#searchbox/\" title=\"Find your local Citizens Advice office\">Find your local Citizens Advice office.</a></p>\n\n<p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.lawsociety.org.uk/choosingandusing/findasolicitor.law\" title=\"Find a solicitor or advice agency\">Find a solicitor or advice agency.</a> </p>\n\n<p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://england.shelter.org.uk/get_advice/paying_for_a_home/tenancy_deposits/deposit_protection_schemes/\" title=\"Tenancy deposit protection scheme advice from Shelter\">Deposit protection scheme advice from Shelter.</a></p>\n"}]},"tags":[{"title":"Owning and renting a property","id":"https://www.go